FAITH Personal and Non-Commercial Use License

1. Definitions

For the purposes of this license:

- "Commercial use" means any use for the benefit of a business, client,
  employer, legal entity, revenue-generating activity, paid service, paid
  product, paid work, consulting engagement, contract, freelance engagement, or
  self-employment activity.
- "Personal use" means use by a natural person acting for themselves and not
  for the benefit of a business, client, employer, legal entity, or
  revenue-generating activity.
- "Internal non-profit use" means use only within the permitted organisation
  for its own internal non-profit purposes, and not for the benefit of clients,
  customers, third parties, or affiliated commercial entities.
- "Written permission" means express written approval from the copyright
  holder.

2. Grant of Permission

You may use, copy, fork, modify, and publish this software, and modified
versions of it, for personal and non-commercial purposes only, provided that
this license remains attached to the software and to any modified version.

3. Permitted Non-Commercial Use

The following uses are permitted without separate written permission:

- personal individual use that is not for the benefit of a business, client,
  employer, or revenue-generating activity;
- personal learning, experimentation, and hobby use;
- use by a registered charity for its own internal non-profit use only, with no
  parent company, subsidiary, sister company, or affiliated commercial entity
  benefiting from that use;
- use by schools, colleges, and universities for their own internal
  non-profit educational use only;
- use by students for their own personal non-commercial use.

4. Commercial and Restricted Use

You may not use this software, or any modified version of it, for the benefit
of a business, client, employer, or revenue-generating activity without prior
written permission from the copyright holder.

For the avoidance of doubt, freelance work, contracting, consulting,
self-employment, sole-trader activity, one-person business activity, and use
through a company or other legal entity are all classed as commercial use when
they benefit a business, client, employer, or revenue-generating activity.

For the avoidance of doubt, use by a registered charity, school, college, or
university is permitted only for that organisation's own internal non-profit
use. It is not permitted where that use benefits any client, external third
party, affiliated commercial entity, parent company, subsidiary, or sister
company.

Without prior written permission from the copyright holder, you may not:

- use this software within or for a company, business, government body,
  nonprofit organisation other than a registered charity as described above, or
  any other legal entity;
- use this software as part of paid work, client work, consulting, contracting,
  or employment;
- use this software to maintain, modify, support, operate, or further develop
  software after that software has first been sold, licensed for a fee, or used
  to provide paid services to another party;
- use this software to provide a hosted service or managed service to third
  parties;
- sell this software;
- sublicense this software under different license terms.

For the avoidance of doubt, an individual may create software using FAITH for
their own personal non-commercial use, and the copyright holder makes no claim
over that output. However, once that software has first been sold, licensed for
a fee, or used to provide paid services to another party, FAITH may no longer
be used on that software without prior written permission from the copyright
holder.

